dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers module¶

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.aggregate_responses(predicate)¶

Checks if predicate needs to be answered 0 more times. If uncertainty criteria are met, combines worker responses into one value for the predicate. Otherwise, adds five to the appropriate predicateStatus so that more answers will be collected.

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.decrementStatus(index, restaurant)¶

decrease the status by 1 once an answer has been submitted for that predicate

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.eddy(ID, numOfPredicates)¶

Uses a random lottery system to determine which eligible predicate should be evaluated next.

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.eddy2(ID, numOfPredicates)¶
dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.findRestaurant(predicateBranch, ID)¶

Finds the restaurant with the highest priority for a specified predicate such that the relevant worker has not answered the relevant question about the restaurant.

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.findTotalTickets(pbSet)¶

Finds the total number of “tickets” held by a set of PredicateBranches, by turning selectivity into a useful integer. Selectivity = (no’s)/(total evaluated)

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.incrementStatus(index, restaurant)¶

increases the status by 2 because the answer is not certain

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.markFailed(predicate)¶

Set all predicate status fields to -1 to indicate that it needs no further evaluation (because it has failed a predicate)

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.printQuerySet(qs)¶
dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.printResults()¶

If there are no more predicates to be evaluated, print the restaurants satisfying all predicates to the terminal.

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.randomAlgorithm(ID, numOfPredicates)¶

Randomly selects the next predicate from the available choices.

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.runLottery(pbSet)¶

runs the lottery algorithm

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.runLotteryWeighted(pbSet)¶

runs the lottery algorithm

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.runLotteryWeightedWithMemory(pbSet)¶

runs the lottery algorithm

dynamicfilterapp.views_helpers.updateCounts(pB, task)¶

updates the predicate branch’s total and “No!” counts relative to the confidence levels
